  accentWord="Security"
  subhead="A homeowner finds your website at 11:30pm on a Friday. Two hours ago, someone tried to force the back door of her 1930s semi in Summertown — the door frame is splintered, the lock is damaged, and the police are creating a crime number. Her partner is fitting a temporary padlock. She has no alarm, no cameras, and no security lighting. Her insurance renewal is approaching and her policy now likely requires an NSI or SSAIB approved alarm system. She types: 'Our back door was just forced tonight — attempted burglary. Police are involved. We have no alarm or cameras. We want a proper security system — alarm with police monitoring, cameras covering the front and back of the house, a video doorbell, and security lighting. I think our insurance will require an approved installer. The house is a 1930s semi, three bedrooms, side passage to the back garden. We want this done as soon as possible — we do not feel safe. We are in Summertown.' Without chat, she bookmarks and calls three firms on Monday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your NSI Gold approval and asks about the number of ground-floor windows and whether the side passage has a gate. She confirms eight ground-floor windows, no side gate. Saturday morning you call: Summertown 1930s 3-bed semi, attempted burglary Friday night, splintered back door, no existing security, alarm with police monitoring, CCTV front and back, video doorbell, security lighting, 8 ground-floor windows, no side gate, insurance requirement, urgent."
  scenario="It is 2am on a Saturday. A hotel general manager types: 'Hello — we operate a 40-room boutique hotel in Woodstock. Our current CCTV system — twelve old analogue cameras — has failed completely. The NVR hard drives have crashed and we have no recording capability. We also need access control on the spa and gym for guests only, and a video intercom replacement at the main entrance. Our insurance requires NSI approved CCTV with minimum 30-day recording retention. We have a major wedding on site in three weeks and need the system operational before then — 150 guests arriving and we cannot operate without functioning CCTV. Can your team survey early next week and complete the installation before the wedding? Budget is approved for the full upgrade.' Without chat, he sleeps and emails Monday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your NSI approval and asks about the existing cabling infrastructure and whether the hotel operates POE network switches. He confirms Cat5e cabling exists to most camera positions. Monday you call: Woodstock 40-room boutique hotel, 12 analogue cameras failed NVR crash, Hikvision/Dahua IP upgrade, 30-day retention insurance requirement, spa/gym access control, main entrance video intercom, Cat5e existing, wedding 150 guests 3 weeks, NSI approved, budget approved."
  benefits={benefits}
